Vice President Biden issued a statement expressing his satisfaction with the Senate's confirmation of Chief Gil Kerlikowske as Director of the Office of National Drug Control Policy. Biden believes that Kerlikowske, with his extensive law enforcement experience, is the right person for the job. The statement emphasizes that Kerlikowske has been actively involved in combating drugs for over 36 years and that he will lead the nation's efforts against illegal drugs with unwavering determination.